pelvishipright.label: Hip Ranges of Motion Table A-3 page 598: AMA Estimated Normal: Flexion (100D), Extension (30D), Abduction (40D), Adduction (20D) External Rotation (50D), Internal Rotation (40D). Motion is measured with goniometer and is reported right over left side in Degrees (D).

Actual goniometer measurements of the range of motion are only required for PR-4 (Permanent & Stationary) reports. Visual estimates of the range of motion may be adequate for Doctor's First reports and PR-2 reports.
